{
  "caption_en": "Table S9. Bootstrap 95 % confidence intervals for GEV-derived return levels of CHIRPS daily extreme-precipitation indices (Rx1day, Rx5day) over Imbabura Province, 1981–2024 (n = 44 years). Each interval is constructed from 50 bootstrap replicates of the annual maxima series (sampling with replacement, random seed = 42), with each replicate fit by maximum-likelihood GEV (scipy.stats.genextreme). Replicates with shape parameter |ξ| > 0.4 or scale σ < 1 mm and return levels exceeding 3× the observed maximum were rejected as numerically unstable. Bands: B1 (<2000 m, western basin), B2 (2000–2800 m, inter-Andean), B3 (>2800 m, high), and ALL (province-wide aggregation). The widening of the CI with longer return periods reflects the limited series length and is consistent with extreme-value-statistics expectations.",
